      "side": 0,
      "message": "Sounds like a good guess.\n\nThe thing is, text blobs should be able to compute their (conservative) bounds even in the absence of client hints (when fDeferredBounds \u003d\u003d true): https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/skia/src/core/SkTextBlob.cpp?rcl\u003dfad5c773f7b60d2528dae4ccefef7bb5501f0f7b\u0026l\u003d300\n\nWith some instrumentation, I\u0027m seeing empty bounds being computed whenever the failures are triggered.\n\nSo, for whatever reason, glyph-bounds-related font methods (SkFontPriv::GetFontBounds, SkFont::getBounds) don\u0027t appear to work with deserialized typefaces?\n\nE.g. https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/skia/tests/SkRemoteGlyphCacheTest.cpp?rcl\u003dfad5c773f7b60d2528dae4ccefef7bb5501f0f7b\u0026l\u003d604",
